SECOND AMENDED AND RESTATED COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS SECOND AMENDED AND RESTATED COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this ???Agreement???) is entered into as of the 25th day of January, 2022, by and among BP Wind Energy North America Inc., a Delaware corporation (together with its successors and assigns, ???BPWENA???), Flat Ridge 2 Wind Energy LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and assigns, ???Flat Ridge 2???), Flat Ridge 3 Wind Energy, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and assigns, ???Flat Ridge 3???), Flat Ridge 4 Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and assigns, ???Flat Ridge 4???), as successor-in-interest to AEP Renewables Development, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, f/k/a SGS Development, LLC (???ARD???), and Flat Ridge 5 Wind Energy LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and assigns, ???Flat Ridge 5???), and each of Flat Ridge 5, BPWENA, Flat Ridge 2, Flat Ridge 3 and Flat Ridge 4 and any assignee pursuant to Section 11.3 may hereinafter be referred to individually as a ???Party??? or together as the ???Parties???). Flat Ridge Interconnection LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (???Flat Ridge Interconnection???), joins this Agreement solely for the purposes specified in Section 7.2(c).
RECITALS:
WHEREAS, BPWENA and its Affiliates (as defined below) originally, and Flat Ridge 2, Flat Ridge 3, Flat Ridge 4, and any of their successors and assigns, intend to develop a series of wind and/or solar power electric generating and/or storage facilities located in Barber, Harper, Kingman and Sumner Counties, Kansas (collectively, the ???Project???), in multiple phases, each of which is or will be owned by a separate project company (each a ???Phase??? and collectively the ???Phases???).
WHEREAS, Flat Ridge 2 has developed the initial Phases of the Project, which consist of (a) the ???Flat Ridge 2??? wind farm located in Barber, Harper, Kingman and Sumner Counties, Kansas with a combined nameplate capacity of approximately 419.2 MW and (b) the ???Flat Ridge 2 South??? wind farm located in Harper County, Kansas, with a combined nameplate capacity of approximately 51.2 MW (together, the ???FR2 Phase???);
WHEREAS, in furtherance of the development of the FR2 Phase, in accordance with the Capital Contribution Agreement dated December 2, 2011, by and among BPWENA, Flat Ridge 2 Holdings LLC, Flat Ridge 2 Wind Holdings LLC and Flat Ridge 2, and the Capital Contribution Agreement (Expansion) dated June 13, 2012, by and among BPWENA, Flat Ridge 2 Holdings LLC, Flat Ridge 2 Wind Holdings LLC and Flat Ridge 2 (collectively, the ???FR2 Phase CCA???), BPWENA assigned to Flat Ridge 2 certain assets and rights in connection with the development of the FR2 Phase;
WHEREAS, development is contemplated of additional Phases of the Project beyond the FR2 Phase (each, an ???Additional Phase???) from time to time;
WHEREAS, pursuant to the FR2 Phase CCA, BPWENA reserved certain rights (the ???Reserved Rights???) with respect to the FR2 Phase assets for the development of Additional Phases, including an undivided interest in certain of the real property on which the FR2 Phase and the Common Facilities (as hereinafter defined) are located;
WHEREAS, in furtherance of the development of each Additional Phase, prior to the Connection (as hereinafter defined) of such Additional Phase, BPWENA intends to assign to the applicable project company (each, an ???Additional Phase Project Company???) certain assets and rights (including a pro rata portion of BPWENA???s Reserved Rights) pursuant to a capital contribution agreement or other assignment agreement similar to the FR2 Phase CCA (each, an ???Additional Phase CCA??? and, with the FR2 Phase CCA, each a ???CCA??? and collectively the ???CCAs???);
WHEREAS, BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2 entered into that certain Common Facilities Agreement, dated as of December 12, 2011, by and between BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2, as amended by that certain First Amendment to Common Facilities Agreement, dated as of June 13, 2012, and that certain Second Amendment to Common Facilities Agreement, dated as of April 25, 2014 (as so amended, and as further modified by the joinders described below, the ???Original CFA???), in order to govern the rights and obligations of BPWENA, Flat Ridge 2 and each Additional Phase Owner with respect to the Phases;
WHEREAS, an Additional Phase of the Project is being developed by Flat Ridge 3 and is expected to have a nameplate capacity of up to 128 MW (the ???FR3 Phase???);
WHEREAS, in furtherance of the development of the FR3 Phase, (a) in accordance with the Capital Contribution Agreement dated December 20, 2013, by and between BPWENA and Flat Ridge 3 (the ???FR3 Phase CCA???), which is an Additional Phase CCA, BPWENA assigned to Flat Ridge 3 certain assets and rights in connection with the development of the FR3 Phase, and (b) Flat Ridge 3 executed and delivered that certain Joinder to Common Facilities Agreement dated December 20, 2013, as a result of which Flat Ridge 3 became a party to the Original CFA;
WHEREAS, an Additional Phase of the Project is being developed by Flat Ridge 4 with an expected nameplate capacity of up to 134 MW (the ???FR4 Phase???);
WHEREAS, in furtherance of the development of the FR4 Phase, (a) in accordance with the Assignment and Assumption Agreement dated December 20, 2013, by and between BPWENA and ARD (the ???FR4 Phase CCA???), which is an Additional Phase CCA, BPWENA assigned to ARD certain assets and rights in connection with the development of the FR4 Phase, and (b) ARD executed and delivered that certain Joinder to Common Facilities Agreement dated December 20, 2013, as a result of which ARD became a party to the Original CFA;
WHEREAS, the Parties (who are all of the Parties to the Original CFA) amended and restated the Original CFA, which Amended and Restated Common Facilities Agreement (the ???Initial A&R CFA???) became effective by its terms on March 22, 2021, and which laid out a framework under which the Phases will share in the use, ownership and cost of certain electrical transmission, operations and maintenance, communications and other facilities and associated real property rights and to engage the Common Facilities Manager (as hereinafter defined) to repair, manage, operate and maintain the foregoing, all on the terms and conditions set forth herein;
WHEREAS, the Parties (who are all of the Parties to the Original CFA and the Initial A&R CFA) wish to again amend and restate via this Agreement to allow for the option of Phases being developed using solar and/or storage technology rather than only wind;
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual agreements herein contained and other good and valuable consideration, receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows:

For purposes of this definition, the ???nameplate capacity??? of (a) the FR2 Phase shall not exceed 470.4 MW, (b) the FR3 Phase shall not exceed 128 MW, (c) the FR4 Phase shall not exceed 134 MW, and (d) the FR5 Phase shall not exceed 150 MW. 1.2 Rules of Interpretation.
(a) All article, section, schedule, and exhibit references used in this Agreement are to articles, sections, schedules and exhibits of or to this Agreement unless otherwise specified. The schedules and exhibits attached to this Agreement constitute a part of this Agreement and are incorporated herein for all purposes.
(b) If a term is defined as one part of speech (such as a noun), it shall have a corresponding meaning when used as another part of speech (such as a verb). Terms defined in the singular have the corresponding meanings in the plural, and vice versa. Unless the context of this Agreement clearly requires otherwise, words importing the masculine gender shall include the feminine and neutral genders and vice versa. The term ???includes??? or ???including??? shall mean ???including without limitation.??? The words ???hereof,??? ???hereto,??? ???hereby,??? ???herein,??? ???hereunder??? and words of similar import, when used in this Agreement, shall refer to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular section or article in which such words appear. The word ???or??? shall not be exclusive.
(c) This Agreement shall be construed without regard to any presumption or rule requiring construction or interpretation against the drafting Party or the Party causing any instrument to be drafted.
(d) The captions and headings in this Agreement are for convenience only and shall not be considered a part of or affect the construction or interpretation of any provision of this Agreement.
(e) References to ???this Agreement??? or any other agreement or document shall be construed as a reference to such agreement or document, including any exhibits appendices and schedules thereto, as amended, amended and restated, modified or supplemented and in effect from time to time.
ARTICLE II. EFFECTIVENESS 2.1 Effective Date of Initial A&R CFA. By its terms, the Initial A&R CFA Effective Date (as defined therein) occurred on March 22, 2021, and the Original CFA was superseded in all respects. The Parties acknowledge the ongoing obligation to cause the events set forth on Schedule 2 to occur as soon as practicable in the order set forth on Schedule 2.
2.2 Effectiveness Conditions. This Agreement shall become effective upon execution, subject to any FERC approval as discussed in Section 6.2(e). The Initial A&R CFA, and appropriate certificates of concurrence, were accepted and approved by FERC. See Flat Ridge Interconnection LLC, 174 FERC ?? 61,004 (January 5, 2021). Once effective, this Agreement shall supersede the Initial A&R CFA in all respects. ARTICLE III. COMMON FACILITIES
3.1 Common Facilities. The Parties intend for certain operations and maintenance, communications and other facilities and assets that will be procured, installed, and constructed for the FR2 Phase and Additional Phases to be commonly used and owned by the Phases, along with
the Shared Agreements and Shared Permits (collectively, the ???Common Facilities???). Facilities may be designated as Common Facilities in accordance with Section 3.4. The Common Facilities shall not include the following facilities (the ???Excluded Facilities???):
(a) any site access roads built by any Phase; provided that each Phase may use the access roads built by any other Phase, at no cost to the Phase that uses such roads;
(b) the medium-voltage power collection system and electric meters owned by any Phase, even though connected to Common Facilities, or any WTGs, solar or storage facilities of any Phase; or
(c) any other facilities or equipment not designated as Common Facilities pursuant to Section 3.4 from time to time.
3.2 Shared Real Property. The Common Facilities will be located on certain real property that is subject to the easement, lease, option or fee interests described under Exhibit B-1 from time to time (collectively, the ???Shared Real Property???). Upon the designation of any Common Facilities as Common Facilities pursuant to Section 3.4, the Parties shall update Exhibit B-1 to reflect the designation of the real property underlying such Common Facilities as Shared Real Property and the Pro Rata Share of each Phase in each of such Shared Real Property. Any real property right of a Party that is not included as Shared Real Property shall be an excluded real property right (the ???Excluded Real Property???).
3.3 Access. Each Party shall have a non-exclusive right of access (a) to the Common Facilities as reasonably necessary to ensure that the Common Facilities remain operational and that the obligations of the Common Facilities Manager are being met and (b) over any Shared Real Property, provided however, that such access shall not in any way materially interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Parties of their respective rights in such Shared Assets or other rights arising under this Agreement. In addition to the foregoing access rights, Flat Ridge 2 hereby grants to Flat Ridge 3 a non-exclusive right of access over and across the FR2 Phase site to the Common Facilities as reasonably necessary to accomplish the purposes set forth in clause (a) of the preceding sentence. No portion of the Shared Real Property may be terminated, modified or amended without the consent of all of the Parties owning an undivided interest in such Shared Real Property.
3.4 Designation of Common Facilities. The Parties acknowledge and agree that, as of the Effective Date, the designs of the Additional Phases (other than the FR3 Phase) have not been determined and, therefore, that it is impossible to determine with certainty what assets will need to be shared by the Additional Phases. Exhibit A reflects the facilities, assets, agreements and permits designated as Common Facilities as of the Effective Date. If a Phase Owner requests to designate as a Common Facility a then existing facility or asset that has not already been designated as a Common Facility, the Parties shall undertake commercially reasonable efforts, subject to Section 3.5, to accommodate the needs of such Additional Phase, and the Parties shall update Exhibit A to reflect the designation of such assets as Common Facilities.
3.5 Further Assurances; Assignability of Certain Shared Assets. In the event a Phase Owner at any time during the term of this Agreement determines that an asset was not specifically designated as a Shared Asset but should have been designated as such in accordance with the terms of this Agreement in order for such Phase Owner to construct, operate or maintain its Phase, each

(a) A Phase Owner who wishes to permanently disconnect, abandon and decommission its Phase, unless it elects to preserve its rights pursuant to Section 3.6(b), shall convey its undivided ownership interest in the Shared Assets and assign its rights hereunder to the other Phase Owner(s) at no cost or expense to the other Phase Owner(s) and, thereupon, cease to have any right, title or interest in its undivided ownership interest in the Shared Assets (such Phase Owner, the ???Surrendering Party???). ARTICLE V. OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE; COSTS AND EXPENSES
5.1 Operation and Maintenance. From and after the Effective Date, the Common Facilities Manager will operate and maintain the Common Facilities and Shared Real Property, subject to the direction of the Phase Owners, in accordance with the O&M Agreement. Except as expressly provided to the contrary in this Agreement, the Common Facilities Manager shall, on behalf of the Parties, pay all costs, expenses and Liabilities relating to the design, procurement, construction, installation, startup, use, maintenance, repair, inspection and/or decommissioning of all Shared Assets, and each Party shall reimburse the Common Facilities Manager for its Pro Rata Share of expenses, in each case in accordance with this Agreement and the O&M Agreement. Each Party shall timely and fully discharge its obligations under the O&M Agreement. Design, procurement, construction, installation and startup with respect to any new facilities that are intended to become Common Facilities shall be managed by the Phase Owners of the Phases who will share such Common Facilities and not by the Common Facilities Manager. At the time a newly constructed common facility is placed in service, it shall become a Common Facility and shall thereafter be managed by the Common Facilities Manager. As long as the Common Facilities Manager is performing operation and maintenance services for the Shared Assets or any Phase, the Common Facilities Manager may also use the FR2 Phase O&M Building in connection with the operation and maintenance of any other wind or solar power electric generating facility or electric storage facility in the vicinity of the Project.
5.2 Shared Expenses.
(a) Each Party hereby confirms its obligation to share in the periodic payment of Shared Expenses and agrees, severally but not jointly, to pay its Pro Rata Share of the Shared Expenses as and when due and payable. Notwithstanding the foregoing, to the extent the establishment by an Additional Phase Owner of its respective Phase would cause an increase in the Shared Expense portion of any other Phase Owner, such Additional Phase Owner will be solely responsible for such incremental increase. The Parties will cause the Common Facilities Manager, as authorized agent for each Party, to administer the collection and payment of the Shared Expenses, whether invoiced by each expense payee against a particular Phase or invoiced as an aggregate expense of all Phases. Each Party will pay each invoice for Shared Expenses promptly upon, and in any event within thirty (30) days of, receipt of written notice thereof from the Common Facilities Manager. As it becomes practicable and desirable, the Parties from time to time may designate (in a written agreement executed by the Parties) additional expenses as Shared Expenses to be administered by the Common Facilities Manager in accordance with this Section 5.2. Each further assumption of Shared Expenses may be proposed by any Party, but will only be approved by an amendment to this Agreement.
(b) If any Party (a ???Non-Paying Party???) fails to timely make any required payment of amounts due under this Section 5.2 and such failure continues for five (5) Business Days after such Non-Paying Party receives notice of such failure, then any other Party may make such payment on behalf of such Non-Paying Party, and the amount so paid shall be immediately due and payable, upon written notice, from the Non-Paying Party to such other Party, together with interest from
the date paid until paid to such other Party at the Default Rate. Such remedy shall be in addition to the right of such other Party to pursue any other remedies that may be available to it under applicable law or this Agreement.
5.3 Capital Costs. To compensate each existing Phase Owner for having borne a disproportionate share of the costs and expenses of design, procurement, construction, installation and/or startup of the Common Facilities, on or prior to the date of Connection of each Additional Phase, such Additional Phase Owner shall compensate each existing Phase Owner using each Common Facility that will be shared by such Additional Phase for a share of the costs and expenses disproportionately borne by each existing Phase Owner as will result in each Phase Owner that is using each of the Common Facilities having borne its Pro Rata Share of the costs and expenses of design, procurement, construction, installation and/or startup of such Common Facilities, in each case based on the book value as of the end of the most recent month prior to the date the reimbursement payment is made.
5.4 No Other Payments. Other than as expressly set forth in this Agreement or the O&M Agreement, no Party will be entitled to any compensation or reimbursement from any other Party as a result of any Phase Owner???s use or ownership of any Shared Assets in accordance with this Agreement.
5.5 Excluded Liabilities. Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, each Party shall be solely responsible for all expenses and other Liabilities relating to the acquisition, design, installation, construction, use, operation, management, maintenance and repair of its Phase and its respective Excluded Facilities and Excluded Real Property; provided, however, this provision shall not give rise to any rights of indemnification under this Agreement except to the extent of indemnification provided hereunder for failure to make payments for Liabilities for the Shared Assets as required pursuant to this Article V. 6.1 Use of Common Facilities. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each Phase Owner shall have the right to use each Shared Asset for its Phase to the extent of its Pro Rata Share in such Shared Asset, including, to the extent applicable, the capacity of the Shared Interconnection Facilities to transmit power bi-directionally from and to such Phase in an amount up to its Pro Rata Share not to exceed, in the aggregate, the Aggregate Capacity of the Shared Interconnection Facilities. (a) No Party shall create, permit or suffer to exist by, through or under such Party or such Party???s Affiliates and its and their respective directors, managers, officers, shareholders, partners, members, employees, contractors, agents and representatives, any liens on the Shared Assets or on the undivided ownership interests or Phase of another Party, except for (i) liens for taxes that are not yet delinquent or are being contested in good faith by appropriate proceedings,
and (ii) carriers???, warehouseman???s, mechanics???, materialmen???s, repairmen???s or other like liens, that arise from the construction, reconstruction, ownership or operation of the Common Facilities; provided, that if any mechanics??? liens or similar liens attach to the Shared Assets, the Party performing or contracting or causing the engagement of the holder of such attached lien shall, within thirty (30) days after it receives notice of the filing, either bond around such lien or establish appropriate reserves therefor, or otherwise remove such lien pursuant to applicable law (each of (i) and (ii), a ???Permitted Lien???). (c) Upon reasonable request of a Party, each other Party shall cooperate in the financing or refinancing of each Phase, including the execution of estoppels, consents and other similar agreements with respect to the collateral assignment as may be reasonably requested by the requesting Party or its Lenders, and in the making of any filings reasonably required by such requesting Party for regulatory compliance, which are customary for comparable transactions and consistent with the terms hereof, all solely at the expense of the requesting Party and at no out-of-pocket costs to any other Party. (a) For the duration of this Agreement, Common Facilities Manager or another Party agreed upon by the Parties (the ???Designated Party???) shall procure property and liability insurance policies for the Shared Assets on behalf of all Parties as described in Exhibit D (the ???Common Insurance???), and the Phase Owners shall bear responsibility for premiums and deductibles therefor based on their Pro Rata Shares. property insurance policy and cause their insurers to waive rights of subrogation; provided that the foregoing waiver shall not be deemed a waiver by any owner of claims related to the failure of any other owner to maintain an insurance policy required by this Agreement.
(b) The Designated Party shall provide the other Parties with insurance certificates reasonably acceptable to the other Parties evidencing that insurance coverages are in compliance with this Agreement. All Common Insurance and certificates shall, to the extent permitted by law, (a) name Common Facilities Manager as a named insured (including Flat Ridge Interconnection with respect to liability insurance set forth in Exhibit D) and each of the other Parties as a named insured or an additional insured (as applicable) under the Commercial General Liability, Automobile Liability and Umbrella Liability Policies for their liability arising out of the operations of the Common Facilities as described in this Agreement and (b) provide a waiver of any rights of subrogation against each of the other Parties. (c) If any insurance required to be maintained by a Party hereunder ceases to be available on commercially reasonable terms in the commercial insurance market, such Party shall provide written notice to the other Parties, accompanied by a certificate from an independent insurance advisor of recognized national standing, certifying that such insurance is not available on commercially reasonable terms in the commercial insurance market for electric facilities of similar type, geographic location and design. 6.4 No Public Access or Dedication of Property. There shall be no general public access to any Shared Assets. Each Party agrees that (a) no Party dedicates to public or quasi-public use or purpose any of the Shared Assets or other facilities which are the subject of this Agreement, and (b) the execution of this Agreement shall not, nor shall any performance or partial performance of this Agreement, be or ever be deemed, asserted or urged by any Party to be a dedication to public or quasi-public use of the Shared Assets, or any property of any other Party.

administered by the Common Facilities Manager.

Each Party shall, with respect to its respective Phase and its respective Excluded Facilities and Excluded Real Property, comply with the terms of the Shared Real Property Agreements, Shared Agreements and Shared Permits. In the event of a curtailment of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, whether by the Common Facilities Manager pursuant to the O&M Agreement or by the Interconnection Provider, Transmission Operator or a Governmental Authority, and unless otherwise directed by the Interconnection Provider, Transmission Operator or a Governmental Authority, each Phase shall be curtailed based on its Pro Rata Share of the Shared Interconnection Facilities; provided, however, in the event the need for the interruption or reduction can be attributed to or was requested by the owner of a particular Phase, then, to the extent possible, such interruption or reduction shall be limited to such Phase. ARTICLE X. EVENTS OF DEFAULT; REMEDIES AND INDEMNIFICATION
10.1 Events of Default. The occurrence and continuation of any of the following events at any time during the term of this Agreement shall constitute an event of default of a Party (an ???Event of Default???):
(a) The Party fails to pay when due any amounts required to be paid under this Agreement, and such failure to pay is not cured within ten (10) days following written notice from any other Party or the Common Facilities Manager specifying the amount to be paid, provided that such period shall be extended for so long as the allegedly defaulting Party is disputing in good faith such amount pursuant to the procedures set forth in Section 11.5;
(b) The Party fails to perform any other covenant or obligation under this Agreement within thirty (30) days following written notice from any other Party specifying the nature of the failure to perform, provided that if the breach is not reasonably capable of being cured within thirty (30) days, then the breach shall be deemed cured if the defaulting Party commences, diligently pursues, and completes action that remedies the default within ninety (90) days of receipt of such notice;
(c) Any substantial part of such Party???s property is subjected to any levy, seizure, assignment or sale for or by any creditor or Governmental Authority that materially affects that Party???s ability to perform under this Agreement; or
(d) The Party is adjudicated as bankrupt, becomes insolvent, enters into an arrangement or composition with such Party???s creditors, suffers permanent or temporary court- appointed receivership of substantially all of such Party???s property, makes a general assignment for the benefit of creditors, files a voluntary bankruptcy petition or suffers the filing of an involuntary bankruptcy petition that is not dismissed within sixty (60) days after filing.
10.2 Remedies. Upon the occurrence and during the continuation of an Event of Default by a Party, each other Party shall have any and all of the following remedies:
(a) In its sole and absolute discretion, to cure the default of the defaulting Party by making or tendering the required payment or performance, and permitting the defaulting Party???s Phase to remain connected to the Common Facilities and sales of electricity by the defaulting Party to be continued; if any Party elects to cure an Event of Default of another Party, the defaulting Party shall reimburse the curing Party for its expenses incurred in rendering the cure, plus interest at the Default Rate;
(b) To require that the Common Facilities Manager disconnect the defaulting Party???s Phase from the Common Facilities; provided, that the defaulting Party???s Phase shall be permitted to reconnect promptly when and if (i) the default is cured, and (ii) any and all damages suffered
and incurred by the non-defaulting Parties have been compensated in a manner consistent with this Agreement and the O&M Agreement, with interest paid at the Default Rate; provided further, that no Party shall have the right to disconnect any Phase from the Common Facilities other than in accordance with this Section (b); (c) To specifically enforce the provisions of this Agreement; the Parties agree that damages may be an inadequate remedy for an Event of Default under this Agreement and that each Party shall be entitled to injunctive and other equitable relief against any other Party, without policy bond or surety, to prevent or eliminate such default; or
(d) To exercise any and all other rights and remedies which the non-defaulting Parties might otherwise have under this Agreement, at law or in equity.
10.3 Remedies Cumulative. Except as otherwise provided herein, no right, remedy or election given by any term of this Agreement shall be deemed exclusive but each shall be cumulative with all other rights and remedies available under this Agreement, at law or in equity.

(i) In the event of a Dispute, the Disputing Parties will use all reasonable efforts to reach a satisfactory solution by referring the Dispute to senior management of each of the Disputing Parties. (ii) Senior management of the Disputing Parties will meet as soon as possible, on no less than seven (7) Days??? written notice, unless specifically agreed otherwise and shall negotiate in good faith. Senior management of the Disputing Parties shall examine any submissions by the Disputing Parties, and shall, if the Dispute cannot be resolved immediately, agree to convene for further negotiations aimed at resolving the Dispute.
(iii) Should senior management of the Disputing Parties be unable to resolve the Dispute within thirty (30) Days after commencement of negotiation by such senior management, any Party may, by delivery of written notice to the other Parties, submit the Dispute to binding arbitration in accordance with Section 11.5(c).
(c) Binding Arbitration.
(i) If a Dispute remains unresolved after the discussions of senior management of the Disputing Parties in accordance with Section 11.5(b) hereof, or if any Disputing Party fails to comply with any of the time periods set forth in Section 11.5(b) above, the Disputing Parties agree that upon prior written notice to the other Disputing Parties, any Disputing Party may submit such Dispute to binding arbitration and that all such Disputes shall be finally settled by binding arbitration, pursuant to the rules of the American Arbitration Association (the ???AAA???), by (subject to the first clause of Section 11.5(c)(ii)) a panel of arbitrators who are to be appointed in accordance with the said rules and who, to the extent possible, shall have experience and expertise in the subject matter involved in the Dispute.
(ii) Unless all Disputing Parties can agree in writing on a single arbitrator within ten (10) Days after the delivery of notice referred to in Section 11.5(b), then, within ten (10) Days thereafter, the Disputing Parties shall each notify the other in writing of the name of the independent arbitrator chosen by them to participate as a member of panel of arbitrators. In the event there are only two Disputing Parties, if a Disputing Party fails to give the other Disputing Party timely notice of such appointment, then the Disputing Party who timely gave such notice shall be entitled to require that its arbitrator act as the sole arbitrator hereunder. If an arbitrator is timely appointed by each of the Disputing Parties, (i) if there is an odd number of Disputing Parties, the arbitration panel shall consist of the arbitrators appointed by each Disputing Party or (ii) if there is an even number of Disputing Parties, the named arbitrators shall select an additional
member of the arbitration panel within ten (10) Days after the named arbitrators have been appointed, and they shall promptly notify the Disputing Parties thereof. Each Disputing Party shall promptly notify the other Disputing Parties and the Disputing Party- selected arbitrators in writing if the additional arbitrator (if any) has any relationship to or affiliation with such Disputing Party (a ???Notice of Relationship???), in which event another arbitrator shall be selected within ten (10) Days after receipt of such Notice of Relationship by the Disputing Party-selected arbitrators. If, in the case of an even number of Disputing Parties, the initially appointed arbitrators cannot timely agree on an additional arbitrator, then any Disputing Party may request that the AAA select the additional arbitrator. The arbitrators, to the extent possible, shall have experience and expertise in the subject matter involved in the Dispute.
(iii) The arbitration hearing shall be held at a site in Houston, Texas, to be agreed to by a majority of the arbitrators on thirty (30) Days??? written notice to the Disputing Parties. The arbitration proceedings shall be held in the English language. (iv) The arbitration hearing shall be concluded within one hundred twenty (120) Days after it is commenced unless otherwise ordered by a majority of the arbitrators on compelling grounds, and the award thereon or decision with respect thereto shall be made within ten (10) Days after the close of the submission of evidence; provided that failure by the arbitrators to conclude the arbitration hearing or make such award or decision within the foregoing deadlines shall not invalidate such arbitration hearing, award or decision. Arbitration demanded hereunder by any Disputing Party shall be final and binding on the Disputing Parties. The decision, arbitration order and relief agreed upon in writing by (A) any two or more of the arbitrators (in the case of a three-member panel) or (B) any four or more of the arbitrators (in the case of a five-member panel) shall be deemed the decision of the panel for all purposes hereof. If the Disputing Party-selected members of the arbitration panel cannot agree, then the decision of the arbitrator not appointed by any Disputing Party shall control. The references herein to the arbitration panel shall also be deemed to refer to a single arbitrator where a panel is not being used hereunder, and all references to decisions, orders, awards and relief granted by the panel of arbitrators shall mean the decision, order, award or relief agreed upon in writing by the required number of members of the panel, as indicated.
(v) The Disputing Parties agree that the arbitration panel may render and the Disputing Parties shall abide by any interim ruling that the arbitration panel deems necessary or prudent regarding discovery, summary proceedings, or other pre-arbitration matters.
(vi) The Parties hereby submit to the in personam jurisdiction of the state and federal courts located in Texas, and agree that any such court may enter all such orders as may be necessary or appropriate to enforce and/or to confirm any ruling or decision or any award rendered by the arbitration panel. Any court of law of Texas, Kansas or the United States of America shall enforce the decision of the panel of arbitrators (or single arbitrator, as applicable) in its entirety and only in its entirety; provided, however, that if a court for any reason refuses to enforce any equitable remedies ordered by the arbitration panel, such refusal shall not affect any damage award made by the arbitration panel.
(vii) Each Party shall bear its own costs or other expenses (including attorneys??? fees and costs) arising out of or occurring because of the arbitration proceedings. Each Party involved in the Dispute shall pay the fees, costs and expenses charged by the arbitrator chosen by it and, in advance, its equal share of the fees, costs and expenses charged by the additional
arbitrator (if any); provided, however, that in the event that there is a single arbitrator, the fees and expenses of such arbitrator shall be borne equally among the Parties involved in the Dispute.
(viii) Third parties dealing with any Disputing Party shall be entitled to fully rely on any written arbitration order or decision with regard to the matters addressed therein, whether or not such arbitration order or decision has been confirmed or adopted by a court, or incorporated in any order of any court.

This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts, each of which when so executed and delivered shall be deemed an original and all of which taken together shall constitute but one and the same instrument. A copy of this Agreement signed by a Party and delivered by facsimile or electronic mail transmission shall have the same effect as the delivery of an original of this Agreement containing the original signature of such first-mentioned Party. 11.9 Third Party Beneficiary. The Lenders are express, third-party beneficiaries of this Agreement. Otherwise, the provisions of this Agreement are intended for the sole benefit of the Parties and there are no other third party beneficiaries.
11.10 Relationship of the Parties. The rights, duties, obligations and liabilities of the Parties under this Agreement will be individual and not joint or collective, and no Party will be responsible for the default of any other Party under this Agreement. It is not the intention of the Parties to create, nor will this Agreement be deemed to create, any partnership, agency, joint venture or trust, or to authorize any Party to act as an agent, servant or employee for any other Party. Each Party will remain solely responsible for the actions of its own directors, officers, and employees.
11.11 Reporting as Direct Owners and Not a Partnership. The Parties hereby agree to elect under Section 761 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, (the ???Code???) to be excluded from the provisions of Subchapter K of Chapter 1 of the Code, with respect to the Shared Assets and to make any corresponding election that may be required for state or local income tax purposes. The Common Facilities Manager shall make the election on behalf of the Parties in the manner prescribed by Treasury Regulation Section 1.761-2(b)(2)(i), effective for the period commencing with the Effective Date. Each Party hereby covenants and agrees to report on its federal, state and local income tax returns all items of income, deduction and credits which result from its undivided ownership interest in the Shared Assets. All such reporting and any tax positions taken with any taxing authority shall be consistent with the exclusion of the Parties from Subchapter K of Chapter 1 of the Code. Further, each Party covenants and agrees not to notify the Commissioner of Internal Revenue that it desires that Subchapter K of Chapter 1 of the Code apply to the Parties.
11.12 Waiver of Subrogation. Each Party waives claims against another Party with respect to loss or damage to the Common Facilities for matters that would be covered by an all-risk property insurance policy covering the waiving Party???s Phase (REGARDLESS OF WHETHER DUE IN WHOLE OR IN PART TO THE NEGLIGENCE OR STRICT LIABILITY OF THE PARTY AGAINST WHICH CLAIMS ARE WAIVED) and to cause its insurers to waive all related rights of subrogation.
11.13 Recording. No Party shall record this Agreement in its entirety. Instead, in accordance with Section 2.3, the Parties shall, on the Effective Date, cause the Memorandum to be recorded in the real property records of each of the counties where Shared Real Property is located.
11.14 Severability. If any portion of this Agreement shall be determined to be invalid or unenforceable, it shall be modified rather than voided, if possible, in order to carry out the intent of this Agreement. In any event, the remainder of this Agreement shall be valid and enforceable
to the fullest extent possible.
11.15 No Waiver. The Parties agree that no failure or delay by a Party in exercising any right, power or privilege under this Agreement shall operate as a waiver thereof, unless such waiver is made expressly and confirmed in writing by the Party against whom such waiver would be enforced, nor shall any single or partial exercise by a Party of any right, power or privilege hereunder preclude any other or future exercise thereof.
11.16 Entire Agreement; Amendments. This Agreement constitutes the entire understanding of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior statements or agreements, whether oral or written, among the Parties with respect to such subject matter. Any modifications, amendments, or changes to this Agreement shall be binding upon the Parties only if agreed upon in writing and signed by the authorized representatives of the Parties.

RECITALS:
WHEREAS, in connection with the joint ownership and use of certain transmission facilities and other assets by the applicable phases of the Flat Ridge wind power electricity generating facility located or that may become located in Barber, Harper, Kingman and Sumner Counties, Kansas, the Parties and AEP Renewables Development, LLC, f/k/a SGS Development, LLC, entered into that certain Amended and Restated Common Facilities Agreement dated as of the date hereof (???CFA???).

WHEREAS, Flat Ridge 2 and BPWENA now desire to transfer to Flat Ridge 3 certain tenant-in-common interests in and to the Shared Real Property, and Flat Ridge 3 desires to accept such transfer.
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual agreements herein contained and other good and valuable consideration, receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
1. Partial Assignment. As of the Effective Date, each of BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2 conveys, assigns and transfers to Flat Ridge 3, and Flat Ridge 3 accepts and assumes:
(a) an undivided tenant-in-common interest in, to and under the agreements set forth on Exhibit A attached hereto, in the percentages required to result in the Parties holding the percentage ownership interests set forth in Exhibit B-1 to the CFA (such transferred interests collectively, the ???FR3 Assigned Interests???); and
(b) all of the obligations, responsibilities and liabilities of BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2 in, to and under the FR3 Assigned Interests, except as described in the CFA;
which acceptance and assumption is subject to all remaining liens, encumbrances and other matters of record that existed as of the first date BPWENA or Flat Ridge 2, respectively, acquired its assigned interest in each of the FR3 Assigned Interests, except as described in the CFA.
2. Representations and Warranties.
BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2 each, as to itself, represents and warrants to and for the benefit of Flat Ridge 3 that, as of the Effective Date:
(a) it has not previously transferred, assigned or encumbered the FR3 Assigned Interests, except for (i) any Permitted Liens, (ii) pursaunt to the terms and conditions of the CFA or (iii) pursuant to that certain Financing Agreement, dated as of December 14, 2012, by and between Flat Ridge 2, the financial institutions from time to time party thereto as lenders and/or fixed rate note purchasers, Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas, as Agent (as defined thereunder) and the other agents and arrangers party thereto (???Financing Agreement???); and
(b) the FR3 Assigned Interests are in full force and effect, the Financing Agreement does not encumber any of the FR3 Assigned Interests, all payments and obligations due from BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2 under said interests are current, and no notices of default, failure or similar have been received by BPWENA or Flat Ridge 2 with respect to any of the FR3 Assigned Interests.
3. Miscellaneous.
(a) Further Assurances. From time to time after the execution and delivery of this Assignment, each Party, at the reasonable request of another Party and without further consideration, shall promptly sign and deliver or cause to be signed and delivered such other instruments of transfer or documents and take such other actions as reasonably may be requested by the requesting Party in order to further evidence or memorialize and give full effect to the transactions contemplated hereunder.
(b) Governing Law. This Assignment shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the internal laws of the State of Kansas, without regard to principles of conflict of laws thereof which may require the application of the law of another jurisdiction.
(c) Binding Effect. The provisions and obligations of this Assignment shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of each Party and its successors and permitted assigns, and constitute covenants running with the land.
(d) Counterparts. This Assignment may be executed in any number of counterparts, each of which when so executed and delivered shall be deemed an original and all of which taken together shall constitute but one and the same instrument. MEMORANDUM OF AMENDED AND RESTATED COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS MEMORANDUM OF AMENDED AND RESTATED COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this ???Memorandum???) is entered into as of , 2020, to be effective as of (???Effective Date???), by and among BP Wind Energy North America Inc., a Delaware corporation (together with its successors and assigns, ???BPWENA???), Flat Ridge 2 Wind Energy LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and assigns, ???Flat Ridge 2???), Flat Ridge 3 Wind Energy, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with its successors and assigns, ???Flat Ridge 3???), and AEP Renewables Development, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, f/k/a SGS Development, LLC (together with its successors and assigns, ???ARD???, and each of BPWENA, Flat Ridge 2, Flat Ridge 3 and ARD and any assignee pursuant to Section Error! RECITALS:
WHEREAS, BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2 entered into that certain Common Facilities Agreement, dated as of December 12, 2011, by and between BPWENA and Flat Ridge 2, as amended by that certain First Amendment to Common Facilities Agreement, dated as of June 13, 2012, and that certain Second Amendment to Common Facilities Agreement, dated as of April 25, 2014 (as so amended, and as further modified by the joinders described below, the ???Original CFA???), in order to govern the rights and obligations of BPWENA, Flat Ridge 2 and each Additional Phase Owner with respect to the Phases;
WHEREAS, an Additional Phase of the Project is being developed by Flat Ridge 3 and is expected to have a nameplate capacity of up to 128 MW (the ???FR3 Phase???);
WHEREAS, in furtherance of the development of the FR3 Phase, (a) in accordance with the Capital Contribution Agreement dated December 20, 2013, by and between BPWENA and Flat Ridge 3 (the ???FR3 Phase CCA???), which is an Additional Phase CCA, BPWENA assigned to Flat Ridge 3 certain assets and rights in connection with the development of the FR3 Phase, and (b) Flat Ridge 3 executed and delivered that certain Joinder to Common Facilities Agreement dated December 20, 2013, as a result of which Flat Ridge 3 became a party to the Original CFA;
WHEREAS, an Additional Phase of the Project is being developed by ARD with an expected nameplate capacity of up to 134 MW (the ???FR4 Phase???);
WHEREAS, in furtherance of the development of the FR4 Phase, (a) in accordance with the Assignment and Assumption Agreement dated December 20, 2013, by and between BPWENA and ARD (the ???FR4 Phase CCA???), which is an Additional Phase CCA, BPWENA assigned to ARD certain assets and rights in connection with the development of the FR4 Phase, and (b) ARD executed and delivered that certain Joinder to Common Facilities Agreement dated December 20, 2013, as a result of which ARD became a party to the Original CFA;
WHEREAS, the Parties (who are all of the Parties to the Original CFA) amended and restated the Original CFA in its entirety pursuant to the Amended and Restated Common Facilities Agreement among the Parties entered into by the Parties as of , 2020 (???Agreement???), to lay out a framework under which the Phases will share in the use, ownership and cost of certain electrical transmission, operations and maintenance, communications and other facilities and associated real property rights and to engage the Common Facilities Manager (as hereinafter defined) to repair, manage, operate and maintain the foregoing, all on the terms and conditions set forth in the Agreement.
SUMMARY AND PUBLIC NOTICE OF CERTAIN AGREEMENT TERMS:
COMMON FACILITIES
1.1 Common Facilities. The Parties intend for certain operations and maintenance, communications and other facilities and assets that will be procured, installed, and constructed for the FR2 Phase and Additional Phases to be commonly used and owned by the Phases, along with the Shared Agreements and Shared Permits (collectively, the ???Common Facilities???). Facilities may be designated as Common Facilities in accordance with Agreement Section 1.4. The Common Facilities shall not include the following facilities (the ???Excluded Facilities???):
(a) any site access roads built by any Phase; provided that each Phase may use the access roads built by any other Phase, at no cost to the Phase that uses such roads;
(b) the medium-voltage power collection system and electric meters owned by any Phase, even though connected to Common Facilities, or any WTGs of any Phase; or
(c) any other facilities or equipment not designated as Common Facilities pursuant to Agreement Section 1.4 from time to time.
1.2 Shared Real Property. The Common Facilities will be located on certain real property that is subject to the easement, lease, option or fee interests described in the Agreement from time to time (collectively, the ???Shared Real Property???). The Shared Real Property as of the Effective Date is described on attached Exhibit A. Upon the designation of any Common Facilities as Common Facilities pursuant to Agreement Section 1.4, the Parties shall update the Agreement to reflect the designation of the real property underlying such Common Facilities as Shared Real Property and the Pro Rata Share of each Phase in each of such Shared Real Property. Any real property right of a Party that is not included as Shared Real Property shall be an excluded real property right (the ???Excluded Real Property???).
1.3 Access. Each Party shall have a non-exclusive right of access (a) to the Common Facilities as reasonably necessary to ensure that the Common Facilities remain operational and that the obligations of the Common Facilities Manager are being met and (b) over any Shared Real Property, provided however, that such access shall not in any way materially interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Parties of their respective rights in such Shared Assets or other rights arising under this Agreement. In addition to the foregoing access rights, Flat Ridge 2 hereby grants to Flat Ridge 3 a non-exclusive right of access over and across the FR2 Phase site to the Common Facilities as reasonably necessary to accomplish the purposes set forth in clause (a) of the preceding sentence. No portion of the Shared Real Property may be terminated, modified or amended without the consent of all of the Parties owning an undivided interest in such Shared Real Property.
1.4 Designation of Common Facilities. The Parties acknowledge and agree that, as of the Effective Date, the designs of the Additional Phases (other than the FR3 Phase) have not been determined and, therefore, that it is impossible to determine with certainty what assets will need to be shared by the Additional Phases. The Agreement reflects the facilities, assets, agreements and permits designated as Common Facilities as of the Effective Date, which include (but are not limited to) the Common Facilities described on attached Exhibit B. If a Phase Owner requests to designate as a Common Facility a then existing facility or asset that has not already been designated as a Common Facility, the Parties shall undertake commercially reasonable efforts, subject to Agreement Section 3.5, to accommodate the needs of such Additional Phase, and the Parties shall update the Agreement to reflect the designation of such assets as Common Facilities.
1.5 Further Assurances; Assignability of Certain Shared Assets. In the event a Phase Owner at any time during the term of the Agreement determines that an asset was not specifically designated as a Shared Asset but should have been designated as such in accordance with the terms of the Agreement in order for such Phase Owner to construct, operate or maintain its Phase, each other Phase Owner agrees, in addition to the requirements set forth in Agreement Section 11.2, to provide such information, execute and deliver any instruments and documents and to take such other actions as may be necessary or reasonably requested by the requesting Phase Owner which are not inconsistent with the provisions of the Agreement and which do not involve the assumption of obligations other than those provided for in the Agreement, in order to give full effect to the Agreement and to carry out the intent of the Agreement. Further, if any
asset designated as a Shared Asset and intended to be Transferred to a Phase Owner pursuant to Agreement Section 4.1 is not assignable without third party consent, such asset shall not Transfer until such consent is obtained; provided, however, that the Phase Owner (or such Phase Owner???s successor-in-interest, if applicable) that originally contracted with such third party to obtain rights with respect to such asset agrees to use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain such rights as are required for the requesting Phase Owner to continue the construction, operation or maintenance of its Phase.
OWNERSHIP AND RIGHT TO USE SHARED ASSETS
1.6 Undivided Interests.
(a) Shared Real Property; Reserved Rights. Flat Ridge 2 was conveyed through the FR2 Phase CCA, and each Additional Phase Project Company was conveyed or will be conveyed through its applicable Additional Phase CCA or in accordance with Agreement Section 4.1(c), an undivided interest, as tenants-in-common, in the Shared Real Property, such that each Phase Owner owns or shall own an undivided interest as tenants-in-common in the Shared Real Property in the amount of its respective Pro Rata Share. Additionally, each Additional Phase Project Company was conveyed or will be conveyed through its applicable Additional Phase CCA, a portion of BPWENA???s Reserved Right for each Additional Phase to obtain an undivided ownership interest in, and non-exclusive right to use on a shared basis, each of the Common Facilities, such that upon the occurrence of each of the Transfers described in Agreement Section 1.6(b), each Phase owns or shall own an undivided interest as tenants-in-common in the Common Facilities in the amount of its respective Pro Rata Share.
(b) Common Facilities. Prior to the date of the Agreement, Flat Ridge 2 constructed and owned one hundred percent (100%) of the initial Common Facilities. Effective upon the date of Connection of each Additional Phase and subject to all required Governmental Approvals, including any required from FERC, and satisfaction of the requirements of Agreement Article II and Section 1.7, each Phase Owner hereby Transfers to each other Phase Owner an undivided interest as a tenant-in-common in all of the Common Facilities to be used by such Additional Phase, such that each Phase owns an undivided interest in such Common Facilities and underlying Shared Real Property Rights in the amount of its respective Pro Rata Share.
(c) Interests in Shared Real Property Not Previously Conveyed. In the event that any Phase Owners intend to jointly own a facility designated (or to be designated) as a Common Facility in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, but one or more of such Phase Owners has not received an undivided interest in the real property rights underlying such Common Facility, then each Phase Owner shall Transfer to each other Phase Owner an undivided interest as a tenant-in-common in all of such real property rights in accordance with its respective Pro Rata Share in the applicable Common Facilities such that each Phase owns an undivided interest in such real property rights, and such real property rights shall become Shared Real Property. The Parties shall update the Agreement from time to time to reflect the addition of any Shared Real Property not already reflected in the Agreement. The undivided interests so Transferred will be memorialized by means of the execution and delivery of an omnibus partial assignment in conformance with the form attached to the Agreement, or such other instrument of transfer in
a form agreed among the applicable Parties. Each such existing Phase Owner will execute and deliver such instrument of transfer as reasonably necessary to effect in each Phase Owner an undivided Pro Rata Share in all Shared Real Property in existence at that time, which shall be recorded in the real property records of the appropriate counties. Accordingly, an undivided tenancy-in-common interest in the Shared Real Property shall be assigned to Flat Ridge 3 pursuant to the Omnibus Partial Assignment, effective as of the Effective Date.
(d) As Is Conveyance. Each Party accepts each of the Shared Assets in their condition existing as of the date of Transfer to such Party of an undivided ownership interest therein, and subject to all laws and all covenants, conditions, reservations, restrictions, easements, liens, encumbrances and other matters affecting the Shared Assets. Except for the representations and warranties in Agreement Section 9.1(e) and in the Omnibus Partial Assignment: all conveyances and transfers to or between the Parties hereunder are made ???AS IS???, ???WITH ALL FAULTS???, AND WITHOUT WARRANTY, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING ANY WARRANTIES OF QUALITY, MERCHANTABILITY, SUITABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, ANY WARRANTIES REGARDING THE EXISTENCE OF ANY SECURITY INTEREST, LIEN OR ENCUMBRANCE AND ANY WARRANTIES ARISING BY COMMON LAW.
(e) Tenancy in Common. The Parties hereby declare that their relationship in and to the Shared Assets will be that of tenants in common, expressly subject, however, to the terms, conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in the Agreement.
(f) Retained/Assumed Liabilities. Each Phase Owner to whom the interests referenced in this Section 1.6 are Transferred (each, a ???Transferee Phase Owner???) shall assume all Liabilities associated with such interests (collectively, the ???Assumed Liabilities???) as of the date of Connection of such Transferee Phase Owner???s Phase (and subject to all required Governmental Approvals, including any required from FERC, and satisfaction of the requirements of Agreement Section 1.7); provided, however, that the Assumed Liabilities shall not include any Liabilities with respect to such interests to the extent such Liabilities:
(i) relate to the Shared Assets but are incurred in connection with acts or omissions occurring prior to such Transfer, including any Shared Expenses incurred prior to such Transfer, or
(ii) excluding the Liabilities described in clause (i), relate solely to another Phase Owner???s individual Phase, Excluded Facilities or Excluded Real Property and not to any Shared Assets
(the Liabilities described in clauses (i) and (ii) collectively, the ???Retained Liabilities???).
Retained Liabilities of the type described in clause (i) above shall be retained by the Phase Owner(s) (other than the Transferee Phase Owner) on a pro rata basis according to their Pro Rata Shares in effect immediately prior to the Transfer to the Transferee Phase Owner. Retained Liabilities of the type described in clause (ii) above shall be retained 100% by the applicable Phase Owner as to each Phase to which such Retained Liabilities relate. Assumed Liabilities
shall be subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and any other agreement among the Phase Owners.
1.7 Connection of Additional Phases.
(a) The Parties acknowledge that the final designs of the Additional Phases (other than the FR3 Phase) have not yet been completed. Prior to the Connection of an Additional Phase, the Party developing such Additional Phase shall have a nonexclusive right to access and use the Common Facilities and the Shared Real Property to the extent reasonably required to Connect such Additional Phase.
(b) At least thirty (30) days prior to Connecting an Additional Phase, such Additional Phase Owner shall notify each other Party and any Lenders of such other Party of which it has notice or knowledge, of the manner in which it intends to connect to any Common Facilities, any modifications or upgrades required to be made to any of the Common Facilities in order to Connect the Additional Phase, and the type and location of the facilities or equipment to be installed, and shall reasonably consider any reasonable request and execute and deliver mutually acceptable documentation with respect thereto as may be reasonably requested by each Party or such Lenders, if any, in order to implement the requirements of the Agreement with respect thereto. The Parties agree that any dispute as to whether a Party has been reasonable in considering suggestions and requests by another Party or its Lenders shall be resolved by the determination of an Independent Engineer. Each Additional Phase Owner shall use commercially reasonable efforts to minimize outages of any other Phase using the applicable Common Facilities, and shall compensate the other Phase Owners for any reasonable, documented losses (including lost revenue), costs and expenses of the existing Phases due to any outage of the Common Facilities during the period of Connection.
(c) Each Party shall take actions reasonably requested by the other Parties, at no costs to the assisting Party, to effect the Connection of each Additional Phase.
(d) Notwithstanding anything contained herein to the contrary, the Additional Phase Owner that is Connecting its Phase shall bear any incremental costs and expenses of modifying and upgrading the applicable existing Common Facilities to accommodate the Connection of its Phase.
1.8 Wind Interference.
(a) The WTGs of the FR2 Phase are located in the locations indicated in the Agreement (the ???Existing Phase WTG Locations???). Upon completion of each Additional Phase, the Agreement shall be updated to include the location of the WTGs of such Additional Phase, which locations shall thereafter constitute Existing Phase WTG Locations.
(b) No Phase Owner (the ???Neighboring Phase Owner???) may construct or install any WTGs within a distance from any Existing WTG Location equal to the greater of one mile or twenty (20) times the rotor diameter of the applicable existing WTG (???Neighboring WTGs???) without the prior written consent of the Phase Owner of the affected Phase (the ???Affected Phase??? and such Phase Owner, the ???Affected Phase Owner???). Notwithstanding the foregoing, a Neighboring Phase Owner may install Neighboring WTGs if an Independent Engineer
determines in writing that the Wind Interference Effects caused by operation of such Neighboring WTGs, in the aggregate, will reduce the total amount of electricity the Affected Phase is expected to deliver for sale in a typical year by no more than 0.3% of the P50 ???Central Estimate??? of energy output for such Affected Phase (as such estimate is determined by such Independent Engineer).
(c) So long as the Neighboring Phase Owner complies with the terms of Agreement Section 1.8(b), each other Phase Owner, for itself and for its Lenders (if applicable), hereby waives, releases and forever relinquishes, any obligation or liability howsoever arising, whether in contract or in tort, of such Neighboring Phase Owner to indemnify or otherwise compensate such existing Phase Owner or its Lenders, if any, for any interference with such existing Phase Owner???s wind resource, disruption of wind flow, wake effect, loss of wind energy and other wind interference effects of any kind (collectively, ???Wind Interference Effects???).
(d) No Phase Owner shall move any of its WTGs from their locations upon the completion of their construction unless such Phase Owner complies with the WTG siting limitations set forth in Agreement Section 1.8(b).
USE OF SHARED ASSETS; RIGHTS AND OBLIGATIONS OF PHASE OWNERS
1.9 Use of Common Facilities. Subject to the terms and conditions of the Agreement, each Phase Owner shall have the right to use each Shared Asset for its Phase to the extent of its Pro Rata Share in such Shared Asset, including, to the extent applicable, the capacity of the Shared Interconnection Facilities to transmit power bi-directionally from and to such Phase in an amount up to its Pro Rata Share not to exceed, in the aggregate, the Aggregate Capacity of the Shared Interconnection Facilities. Notwithstanding the foregoing, (a) no Phase Owner shall use the Shared Assets in connection with any electric generating facilities other than its Phase, and (b) except as otherwise set forth in the Agreement and each CCA, each Phase Owner???s use of the Shared Assets shall not in any way materially interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Phase Owners of their respective rights in such Shared Assets or other rights arising under the Agreement.
1.10 No Public Access or Dedication of Property. There shall be no general public access to any Shared Assets. The Parties shall cooperate in enforcing such requirement for limiting access, including establishing and enforcing procedures for security. Each Party agrees that (a) no Party dedicates to public or quasi-public use or purpose any of the Shared Assets or other facilities which are the subject of the Agreement, and (b) the execution of the Agreement shall not, nor shall any performance or partial performance of the Agreement, be or ever be deemed, asserted or urged by any Party to be a dedication to public or quasi-public use of the Shared Assets, or any property of any other Party.
1.11 Compliance with Agreements and Permits. Each Party shall, with respect to its respective Phase and its respective Excluded Facilities and Excluded Real Property, comply with the terms of the Shared Real Property Agreements, Shared Agreements and Shared Permits. Each Party shall provide a copy of any notice of default with respect to the Shared Real Property Agreements, Shared Agreements and Shared Permits that is received by it to the other Parties
who have an undivided ownership interest in such Shared Real Property Agreements, Shared Agreements and Shared Permits as soon as reasonably practicable, but in any case within three (3) Business Days after receiving such notice of default, regardless of the party or the contract that is alleged to be in default in the notice.
MISCELLANEOUS
1.12 Notices. All notices, requests, demands and other communications made in connection with the Agreement or this Memorandum shall be in writing and shall be deemed to have been duly given on the date of receipt, if personally delivered or if delivered by overnight courier, or five days after mailing if mailed by certified mail, postage prepaid, return receipt requested, addressed as follows:

1.13 Term. The Agreement remains in full force and effect until the first occurrence of one of the following: (a) after one or more Additional Phases have Connected pursuant to the Agreement, a single Party becomes the owner of the entire ownership interest in all of the Shared Assets, (b) the mutual agreement of all the Parties, or (c) otherwise as provided under the Agreement.
1.14 Counterparts. This Memorandum may be executed in any number of counterparts, each of which when so executed and delivered shall be deemed an original and all of which taken together shall constitute but one and the same instrument. A copy of this Memorandum signed by a Party and delivered by facsimile or electronic mail transmission shall have the same effect as the delivery of an original of this Memorandum containing the original signature of such first-mentioned Party, but each Party agrees to also deliver a ???wet ink??? fully executed, dated, and acknowledged original signature to each other Party, and also multiple of such ???wet ink??? originals if a Party elects to record this Memorandum in multiple counties as a duplicate original.
1.15 Recording. The Parties shall record this Memorandum in the real property records of each of the counties where Shared Real Property described on attached Exhibit A is located.
1.16 Interpretation. This Memorandum does not modify the Agreement, and upon any conflict, the Agreement controls. Capitalized terms not defined in this Memorandum are defined in the Agreement.

6.1. Annual Meeting. An annual meeting of the Members may, but shall not be required to, be called by any Member and, if called, shall be held at such time and place as shall be determined by the Members for the purpose of transacting such business as may properly come before the meeting.

Written notice stating the place, day, and hour of the meeting and the purpose or purposes for which the meeting is called shall be delivered no fewer than ten (10) days nor more than thirty (30) days before the date of the meeting by or at the direction of the Manager or the Members calling the meeting, to each Member entitled to vote at the meeting. When any notice is required to be given to any Member, a waiver of the notice in writing signed by the Person entitled to the notice, whether before, at, or after the time stated therein, shall be equivalent to the giving of the notice. If all of the Members shall meet at any time and place, either within or outside of the State of Delaware, and consent to the holding of a meeting at that time and place, then the meeting shall be valid without call or notice, and at the meeting any lawful action may be taken.
